    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> diced onion</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>balsamic sundried tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and<strong> </strong>1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
