    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and return the<strong> browned lamb meatballs </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook, covered for 12-15 min, stirring occasionally, or until the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has reduced to a ragù-like consistency – these are your <strong>Sicilian-style lamb meatballs</strong></p><p>While the meatballs are cooking, wash your<strong> salad </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
